ne 1508":"16 juni 1508","1567":"1567","1466":"1466","1531":"1531","1542":"1542","1508":"1508","1490":"1490","Huntingdon, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Huntingdon, Cambridgeshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridgeshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1466–1567":"1466–1567","1490–1542":"1490–1542","1508–1531":"1508–1531","16 June 1508":"16 June 1508","1567":"1567","1466":"1466","1531":"1531","1542":"1542","1508":"1508","1490":"1490","Huntingdon, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Huntingdon, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Wing","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Weng</i> (Old West Scandinavian <i>Wenge</i>, perhaps originally a nickname from <i>vengi</i> ‘pillow, cushion’).","English and Scottish: habitational name from either Wing in Buckinghamshire or Wing in Rutland. The Buckinghamshire placename probably means ‘the people of Wiwa’, from an Old English personal name <i>Wiwa</i> + the Old English groupname suffix <i>-ingas</i>. The Rutland placename and probably derives from Old Norse <i>vengi</i> ‘field’.","Chinese: Cantonese form of the surname 榮, see   Rong   4."],"variants":[{"name":"Rong","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Guang, Fang, Shuhong, Xiao, Zhao, Bai, Chen, Cheng, Ding, Guan, Guo, Han.","In some cases also Norwegian: habitational name from a farm name in Hordaland related to <i>rong</i> ‘stern (of a boat)’.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 容, meaning ‘tolerate’ or ‘appearance’ in Chinese: (i) from Rong (容), the name of an ancient state (location unknown). (ii) from Rong (容), the name of a post in ancient China held by officials in charge of the management of rituals, ceremonies, and music. (iii) from the personal name of Rong Cheng (容成), an official during the reign of the legendary Huang Di, the ‘Yellow Emperor’ (<i>c.</i> 27th century  BC ), who was said to be the inventor of the first Chinese calendar. (iv) from the personal name of Zhong Rong (仲容), an official during the reign of the legendary Emperor Shun (<i>c.</i> 23rd century  BC ). (v) from Zi Rong (子容), style name of Nan Rong Shi (南容適), also called Nan Rong (南容), a student of Confucius (551–479  BC ) during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Godfredus Wing was born in 1466, in Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Levina D’Grant. He died in 1567, at the age of 101."},"et":{"1466–1567":"1466–1567","1490–1542":"1490–1542","1508–1531":"1508–1531","16 June 1508":"16. juuni 1508","1567":"1567","1466":"1466","1531":"1531","1542":"1542","1508":"1508","1490":"1490","Huntingdon, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Huntingdon, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1466–1567":"1466–1567","1490–1542":"1490–1542","1508–1531":"1508–1531","16 June 1508":"16. kesäkuuta 1508","1567":"1567","1466":"1466","1531":"1531","1542":"1542","1508":"1508","1490":"1490","Huntingdon, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Huntingdon, Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1466–1567":"1466–1567","1490–1542":"1490–1542","1508–1531":"1508–1531","16 June 1508":"16 juin 1508","1567":